title: Woman drowns off inflatable at Adelaide's Aldinga Beach | Daily Mail Online
text: Share this article Share Mr Vaneyk's mother, Erina Morguna, said her son and two others paddled 'like mad' to reach the woman. 'Such a tragic and devastating incident,' she wrote on Facebook on Friday. 'My boy is still in shock and shaken because he and the other two men didn't expect anything terrible had happened until they reached those who were stranded. 'Our hearts go out to the family and friends of this poor woman.' Hundreds of people are said to have witnessed the tragedy, including one who tried to resuscitate the woman. Hundreds of people are said to have witnessed the tragedy, including one who tried to resuscitate the woman The man, named only as Darrell, told The Advertiser : 'I gave two rounds of compression, two breaths. She was unresponsive... the emergency services were here almost immediately.' The woman is thought to have been in the water with a number of people, including her sister. Another witness told the paper: 'When they pulled her back in, the younger woman was yelling ''someone help my sister''... everyone rushed to grab on the inflatable and pulled them in.' The woman is believed to have died at the scene. A police spokesperson said: 'Sadly, the unconscious woman could not be revived, despite the best efforts of paramedics.' It was earlier reported that the woman had been trying to save a nine-year-old girl who was caught in a rip at the popular beach. But police have told Daily Mail Australia that there were no children involved. A report will be prepared for the coroner.
